      <h2>Problem & Motivation</h2>
      <p>
        Existing apps like MeetWays and Midpointr are great for 2 people, but fail when you need to coordinate groups:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Limited to 2-3 people</li>
        <li>Force everyone to use the same travel mode (everyone drives OR everyone uses transit)</li>
        <li>Don't show per-person travel times for each venue suggestion</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        <strong>MeetHalf solves all of these.</strong> It supports 2-8+ people, lets each person choose their own travel mode (driving üöó, transit üöá, or walking üö∂), and shows exact travel times for everyone at each suggested venue.
      </p>

      <h2>How It Works</h2>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Add participants:</strong> Enter names, addresses (with Google autocomplete), and preferred travel modes</li>
        <li><strong>Choose venue type:</strong> Caf√©, restaurant, library, or park</li>
        <li><strong>Get smart suggestions:</strong> Algorithm finds top 5 places optimized for fairness</li>
        <li><strong>Compare options:</strong> See travel time breakdown for each person at each venue</li>
        <li><strong>Navigate:</strong> Click "Open in Google Maps" to get directions</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Fairness Algorithm</h2>
      <p>
        MeetHalf uses a <strong>balanced fairness algorithm</strong> that prioritizes venues where the group's average travel time is minimized:
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Calculate center point:</strong> Geometric average of all participant locations</li>
        <li><strong>Search nearby venues:</strong> Query Google Places API within 3km radius</li>
        <li><strong>Get travel times:</strong> For each venue, calculate travel time for each person using their chosen mode</li>
        <li><strong>Calculate fairness metrics:</strong>
          <ul>
            <li><em>Average time:</em> Mean of all travel times</li>
            <li><em>Max time:</em> Longest individual travel time</li>
            <li><em>Time spread:</em> Difference between max and min times</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Sort by average time:</strong> Venues with lowest average time appear first</li>
        <li><strong>Highlight fair options:</strong> Badge venues where spread ‚â§ 5 minutes (everyone arrives within a similar timeframe)</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="not-prose glass panel p-4 my-6">
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
            <strong>Why average time?</strong> It balances everyone‚Äôs convenience‚Äînobody gets stuck with the 40-minute outlier.
        </p>
    </div>


      <h2>Technical Stack</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Next.js 15:</strong> React framework with server-side rendering</li>
        <li><strong>TypeScript:</strong> Type-safe development with better DX</li>
        <li><strong>Tailwind CSS:</strong> Rapid UI development with utility classes</li>
        <li><strong>Google Maps Platform:</strong> Maps JavaScript API, Places API, Directions API, Geocoding API</li>
        <li><strong>Vercel:</strong> Deployment (coming soon)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Key Features</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Multi-person support:</strong> 2-8+ people (scales to larger groups)</li>
        <li><strong>Per-person travel modes:</strong> Each participant chooses driving, transit, or walking</li>
        <li><strong>Real-time travel times:</strong> Uses Google Directions API for accurate estimates</li>
        <li><strong>Smart venue suggestions:</strong> Top 5 places sorted by fairness + ratings</li>
        <li><strong>Interactive map:</strong> Visual display of participants and suggested venues</li>
        <li><strong>Venue details:</strong> Ratings, price levels, and open hours from Google Places</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Performance Considerations</h2>
      <p>
        For a group of 5 people and 20 candidate venues, the app makes ~100 API calls (5 people √ó 20 venues = 100 directions queries). To handle this efficiently:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>API calls are batched and parallelized</li>
        <li>Results are cached client-side to avoid redundant requests</li>
        <li>Loading states keep users informed (~5-10 seconds for results)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Future Improvements</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Cylindrical search instead of circular (better for groups along a line)</li>
        <li>Save/share meeting plans with a URL</li>
        <li>Allow custom venue types beyond the 4 defaults</li>
        <li>Add preference weighting (e.g., prioritize minimizing one person's time)</li>
        <li>Integration with calendar apps for one-click scheduling</li>
      </ul>

